      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NANGAR MCGRAW (3) boasts a strong record this journey here with three wins and four minors from eight tries. Comes off a (22.52) win last time, scoring by 4.5 lengths in a Grade 4/5 over 400m at this track. Expected to be in the finish. FIRST TRAIN OUT (2) steps out for the first time at this circuit. Missed the frame last time when 4th and beaten 5.5 lengths (20.18) at Goulburn. Should be about the money. LONG DARK ROAD (7) flew around 431m at Gunnedah in 24.96 three back then has been in the money the last two since. Smart winner three back and looks a key chance on that form. HYBRID EVE (1) is another with top-three prospects.",
